<br>
How can you expect punishments to be fair equitable, final and swift... IF theres a possibility of innocent being convicted and punished?<br>
<br>
<br>
Should society pay a price when an innocent is sent to jail or put to death?<br>
<br>
If you could guarantee me that Race, religion, financial status or some other non-consequential facts would not account for convictions... then i would say all crimes should be final and extreme.. Draconian laws would not be bad.<br>
<br>
The problem is that fighting the government is like gambling in vegas or atlantic city.. the house has the odds...<br>
<br>
Have any of you who is in favor of the death penalty ever been arrested? Till you do.. you won't know what police are willing and capable of doing...<br>
<br>
You won't know what it feels to be accused of something you didn't do... spending thousands of dollars to defend yourself and then being found guilty of something you didn;t do.. and a few years downt he line.. someone coming forward and saying hey... i'm sorry didn't do this before.. but remember that stab wound that we said was done by a righthanded person... well the autopsy revealed it was done by a left handed perosn.. and we knew you were right handed there fore you couldn't do it.. but the DA said not to answer more than what was asked... Can you imagine how you would feel?<br>
<br>
Once you are arrested... you are in a loose loose situation.  If you are let go.. your information is already int he system.. if you ar enot let go... then you are charged with offices.<br>
<br>
Once you are charge.. they can at any time drop the charges.. but you are still in system.   <br>
<br>
Lets skip a lot of time money and jump right up to the trial phase... Keep in mind that you can easily spent in the $20k range or more just in the pretrial phase... between paying for investigator to corroborate your claims.. the bail (which you get back if you cover yourself.. but if a bailbonds covers it you pay 10 percent of the bail and you do not get it back no matter what.)  lawyers per hour fees, court filing costs...<br>
<br>
Now.. the trial phase... You spent another $20-30K easy defending yourself... and this is supposedly while remaining innocent until proven guilty...<br>
<br>
So this means you can easily be $20-50K in the hole... and can take from 1-2 years before you go to trial...   THEN you have a 50 50 chance.  <br>
<br>
Worse case scenario.. I could  try and describe it.. but i'll leave it up to you.<br>
<br>
Best case scenario.. they find you not guilty.. you spent a truck load of money either from family and friends or from loans.. or who knows where it came from...  not to mention the stress  lost sleep, pain and shame...<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
